  "content": "### Task 7: Revise IngestionAdapter Trait (D69)\n\n    /// its strategies (e.g., AstChunker) as overrides in the registry.\n    fn register_chunking(&self, registry: &mut crate::chunking_pipeline::FormatRegistry);\n\n    /// Return raw source files for the kernel's ChunkingPipeline.\n    /// Files are returned as-is (content + metadata); the pipeline\n    /// handles all chunking, embedding, and storage.\n    async fn ingest_sources(&self, source_path: &str) -> Result<Vec<crate::chunking_strategy::SourceFile>>;\n}\n```\n\nAlso add to the imports at the top of traits.rs:\n```rust\nuse crate::chunking_pipeline::FormatRegistry;\nuse crate::chunking_strategy::SourceFile;\n```\n\nNOTE: This is a breaking change. The adapter-git crate will fail to compile until Task 8. That's expected — this is a pre-release clean break per D69.\n\n**Step 3: Verify corvia-kernel compiles**\n\nRun: `cargo check -p corvia-kernel`\nExpected: PASS (kernel itself doesn't implement the trait)\n\nRun: `cargo check -p corvia-adapter-git`\nExpected: FAIL (expected — adapter still implements old trait)\n\n**Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add crates/corvia-kernel/src/traits.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(m3.3): revise IngestionAdapter trait — D69 clean break\"\n```\n\n---\n",
